summary: Want a comparison and analysis about what you can determine about Carol Danvers’ history in the Air Force compared to Rhodey’s...
body:
Want a comparison and analysis about what you can determine about Carol Danvers’ history in the Air Force compared to Rhodey’s Air Force career based entirely upon identifying the patches on their uniform? Of course you do!

1) Air Force (Flight) Test Center

The Air Force Flight Test Center was redesignated the Air Force Test Center (AFTC) in 2012. Translated their motto reads “Toward the Unexplored”.

The AFTC is an organization within the Air Foce which broadly develops and conducts testing and evaluation of avionics, flight-control, and weapon systems from concept to deployment. It has test flown every aircraft deployed for the USAF since WWII.

Rhodey wears this patch on his right shoulder (Iron Man 2) and Carol wears it on her left shoulder (EW First Look Photos).

2) Air Force Systems Command // Air Force Materiel Command

Air Force Systems Command was a large command force which conducted R&D specifically for weapons and weapon systems/platforms. In 1992, Air Force Systems Command and Air Force Logistics Command were merged to form the Air Force Materiel Command. Rhodey serves in the successor command force to the one Carol served in approximately 20 years earlier.

Carol (Trailer #1) and Rhodey (Iron Man 2) both wear this patch on the right side of their chest.

3) USAF Test Pilot School - Graduate // USAF Weapons School - Graduate

The U.S. Air Force Test Pilot School trains experimental test pilots, flight test engineers, and flight test navigators to carry out tests and evaluations of new aerospace weapon systems and aircraft of the U.S. Air Force. Pilots are highly adaptive, critical-thinking flight test professionals to lead and conduct full-spectrum test and evaluation of new systems and aircraft.

The U.S. Air Force Weapons School provides advanced training in weapons and tactics employment to officers of the air forces on a variety of different weapons and weapon platforms (i.e. different courses for different planes, tactics, disciplines, etc.).

Carol (Trailer #2) wears her patch on her right shoulder and Rhodey (Iron Man 2) wears his patch on his left shoulder.

TL;DR Carol and Rhodey have very similar Air Force career paths and the differences they have make sense. Carol is the superior pilot, trained to take experimental aircraft and new weapon systems into the skies. Rhodey has more specialty training in evaluating and testing weapons and weapon platforms specifically, which is how he links up with and becomes friends with Tony.
